      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 65,
      "message": "since the allocated size of 'fixedOccurences' is 2, you will get an ArrayIndexOutOfBounds if 'occurences' is larger for some reason. Please consider throwing a meaningful exception according to Gson guidelines. Alternatively, ignore anything beyond the first two elements silently, but try to avoid unexpected failures.\n\nAnd what if 'occurences' is empty? Null? Size of 1? Should 'fixedOccurences' remain { null, null } in this case?\n\nIf your goal is to convert the input \"as is\", consider Object[] fixedOccurrences = new Object[occurences.size()]; or rather the right size - given you skip non-primitives.",
